readme.md

Awesome

   [http://redux.js.org/][68747470733a2f2f7261776769742e636f6d2f6272696c6c
   6f75742f617765736f6d652d72656475782f6d61737465722f72656475782d6c6f676f2
   e737667]

     Redux is a state container for JavaScript apps.

     * Official website: [https://devarchy.com/redux]devarchy.com/redux
     * Use devarchy to add a library to the catalog

Contents

     * Code Architecture
     * Utilities
     * Code Style
     * Dev tools / Inspection tools
     * React Integration
     * Other Integrations
     * Boilerplate
     * Miscellaneous
     * Learning Material
     * Community

Code Architecture

   Aims to improve the overall structure of the source code. Makes
   reasoning about the code easier.
     * [https://github.com/ddsol/redux-schema]redux-schema - Automatic
       actions, reducers and validation for Redux.
     * [https://github.com/gcanti/redux-tcomb]redux-tcomb - Immutable and
       type-checked state and actions for Redux.
     * [https://github.com/cerebral/redux-action-tree]redux-action-tree -
       The Cerebral signals running with Redux.
     * [https://github.com/salsita/redux-elm]redux-elm - The Elm
       Architecture in JavaScript.

Utilities

     * [https://github.com/tommikaikkonen/redux-orm]redux-orm - Small,
       simple and immutable ORM to manage relational data in your Redux
       store.
     * [https://github.com/agraboso/redux-api-middleware]redux-api-middlew
       are - Redux middleware for calling an API.
     * [https://github.com/omnidan/redux-ignore]redux-ignore -
       Higher-order reducer to ignore Redux actions.
     * [https://github.com/calvinfroedge/redux-modifiers]redux-modifiers -
       Collection of generic functions for writing Redux reducers to
       operate on various data structures.
     * [https://github.com/slorber/rereduce]rereduce - Reducer library for
       Redux.
     * [https://github.com/treasure-data/redux-search]redux-search - Redux
       bindings for client-side search.
     * [https://github.com/evgenyrodionov/redux-logger]redux-logger -
       Logger middleware for Redux.
     * [https://github.com/gajus/redux-immutable]redux-immutable -
       Redux-immutable is used to create an equivalent function of Redux
       combineReducers that works with Immutable.js state.
     * [https://github.com/reactjs/reselect]reselect - Selector library
       for Redux.
     * [https://github.com/idolize/redux-requests]redux-requests - Manages
       in-flight requests with a Redux reducer to avoid issuing duplicate
       requests.
     * [https://github.com/omnidan/redux-undo]redux-undo - Higher order
       reducer to add undo/redo functionality to Redux state containers.
     * [https://github.com/dtschust/redux-bug-reporter]redux-bug-reporter
       - Bug reporter and bug playback tool for Redux.
     * [https://github.com/acdlite/redux-transducers]redux-transducers -
       Transducer utilities for Redux.

Store Persistence

     * [https://github.com/michaelcontento/redux-storage]redux-storage -
       Persistence layer for Redux with flexible backends.
     * [https://github.com/rt2zz/redux-persist]redux-persist - Persist and
       rehydrate a Redux store.

Side Effects

   Side Effects / Asynchronous Actions
     * [https://github.com/yelouafi/redux-saga]redux-saga - Alternative
       side effect model for Redux apps.
     * [https://github.com/pburtchaell/redux-promise-middleware]redux-prom
       ise-middleware - Redux middleware for resolving and rejecting
       promises with conditional optimistic updates.
     * [https://github.com/redux-effects/redux-effects]redux-effects - You
       write pure functions, redux-effects handles the rest.
     * [https://github.com/gaearon/redux-thunk]redux-thunk - Thunk
       middleware for Redux.
     * [https://github.com/makeomatic/redux-connect]redux-connect -
       Provides decorator for resolving async props in react-router,
       extremely useful for handling server-side rendering in React.
     * [https://github.com/redux-loop/redux-loop]redux-loop - Port of
       elm-effects and the Elm Architecture to Redux that allows you to
       sequence your effects naturally and purely by returning them from
       your reducers.
     * [https://github.com/salsita/redux-side-effects]redux-side-effects -
       Redux toolset for keeping all the side effects inside your reducers
       while maintaining their purity.
     * [https://github.com/jeffbski/redux-logic]redux-logic - Redux
       middleware for organizing business logic and action side effects.
     * [https://github.com/redux-observable/redux-observable]redux-observa
       ble - RxJS middleware for action side effects in Redux using
       "Epics".
     * [https://github.com/clarus/redux-ship]redux-ship - Composable,
       testable and typable side effects.

Code Style

   Aims to make parts of the source code easier to read/write.
     * [https://github.com/pauldijou/redux-act]redux-act - Opinionated lib
       to create actions and reducers for Redux.
     * [https://github.com/Versent/redux-crud]redux-crud - Set of standard
       actions and reducers for Redux CRUD Applications.

Dev tools / Inspection tools

     * [https://github.com/alexkuz/redux-devtools-inspector]redux-devtools
       -inspector - Another Redux DevTools Monitor.
     * [https://github.com/fcomb/redux-diff-logger]redux-diff-logger -
       Diff logger between states for Redux.
     * [https://github.com/romseguy/redux-devtools-chart-monitor]redux-dev
       tools-chart-monitor - Chart monitor for Redux DevTools.
     * [https://github.com/gaearon/redux-devtools]redux-devtools -
       DevTools for Redux with hot reloading, action replay, and
       customizable UI.
     * [https://github.com/YoruNoHikage/redux-devtools-dispatch]redux-devt
       ools-dispatch - Dispatch your actions manually to test if your app
       Reacts well.
     * [https://github.com/gaearon/redux-devtools-dock-monitor]redux-devto
       ols-dock-monitor - Resizable and movable dock for Redux DevTools
       monitors.
     * [https://github.com/bvaughn/redux-devtools-filterable-log-monitor]r
       edux-devtools-filterable-log-monitor - Filterable tree view monitor
       for Redux DevTools.
     * [https://github.com/gaearon/redux-devtools-log-monitor]redux-devtoo
       ls-log-monitor - The default monitor for Redux DevTools with a tree
       view.
     * [https://github.com/zalmoxisus/remote-redux-devtools]remote-redux-d
       evtools - Redux DevTools remotely.

React Integration

     * [https://github.com/conorhastings/redux-test-recorder]redux-test-re
       corder - Redux middleware to automatically generate tests for
       reducers through ui interaction.
     * [https://github.com/reactjs/react-redux]react-redux - Official
       React bindings for Redux.
     * [https://github.com/keystonejs/react-easy-universal]react-easy-univ
       ersal - Universal Routing & Rendering with React & Redux was too
       hard. Now it's easy.
     * [https://github.com/erikras/redux-form-material-ui]redux-form-mater
       ial-ui - Set of wrapper components to facilitate using Material UI
       with Redux Form.

Routing

     * [https://github.com/Rezonans/redux-async-connect]redux-async-connec
       t - It allows you to request async data, store them in Redux state
       and connect them to your React component.
     * [https://github.com/Agamennon/redux-tiny-router]redux-tiny-router -
       Router made for Redux and made for universal apps. Stop using the
       router as a controller, it's just state.
     * [https://github.com/acdlite/redux-router]redux-router - Redux
       bindings for React Router - keep your router state inside your
       Redux store.
     * [https://github.com/reactjs/react-router-redux]react-router-redux -
       Ruthlessly simple bindings to keep react-router and Redux in sync.
     * [https://github.com/raisemarketplace/ground-control]ground-control
       - Scalable reducer management & powerful data fetching for React
       Router & Redux.

Forms

     * [https://github.com/erikras/redux-form]redux-form - Higher Order
       Component using react-redux to keep form state in a Redux store.
     * [https://github.com/davidkpiano/react-redux-form]react-redux-form -
       Create forms easily in React with Redux.

Component State

     * [https://github.com/threepointone/redux-react-local]redux-react-loc
       al - Local component state via Redux.
     * [https://github.com/tonyhb/redux-ui]redux-ui - Easy UI state
       management for React Redux.

Other Integrations

Flux

     * [https://github.com/acdlite/redux-actions]redux-actions - Flux
       Standard Action utilities for Redux.
     * [https://github.com/acdlite/redux-promise]redux-promise -
       FSA-compliant promise middleware for Redux.

Backbone

     * [https://github.com/redbooth/backbone-redux]backbone-redux - Easy
       way to keep your backbone collections and Redux store in sync.

Falcor

     * [https://github.com/ekosz/redux-falcor]redux-falcor - Connect your
       Redux front-end to your falcor back-end.

RxJS

     * [https://github.com/redux-observable/redux-observable]redux-observa
       ble - RxJS middleware for action side effects in Redux using
       "Epics".
     * [https://github.com/jas-chen/rx-redux]rx-redux - Reimplementation
       of Redux using RxJS.
     * [https://github.com/acdlite/redux-rx]redux-rx - RxJS utilities for
       Redux.
     * [https://github.com/shiftyp/redurx]redurx - Redux'ish Functional
       State Management using RxJS.

Electron

     * [https://github.com/samiskin/redux-electron-store]redux-electron-st
       ore - Redux store enhancer that allows automatic synchronization
       between electron processes.

Deku

     * [https://github.com/troch/deku-redux]deku-redux - Bindings for
       Redux in deku < v2.

Other

     * [https://github.com/netguru/redux-rollbar-middleware]redux-rollbar-
       middleware - Redux middleware that wraps exceptions in actions and
       sends them to Rollbar with current state.
     * [https://github.com/outlandishideas/kasia]kasia - React Redux
       toolset for the WordPress API.

Boilerplate

   Boilerplates / Scaffolds / Starter Kits / Generators / Stack Ensembles
     * [https://github.com/SpencerCDixon/redux-cli]redux-cli - Opinionated
       CLI for building Redux/React apps quicker.
     * [https://github.com/reactuate/reactuate]reactuate - React/Redux
       stack (not a boilerplate kit).
     * [https://github.com/jhen0409/react-chrome-extension-boilerplate]rea
       ct-chrome-extension-boilerplate - Boilerplate for Chrome Extension
       React.js project.
     * [https://github.com/bdefore/universal-redux]universal-redux - Npm
       package that lets you jump right into coding React and Redux with
       universal (isomorphic) rendering. Only manage Express setups or
       Webpack configurations if you want to.
     * [https://github.com/pauldotknopf/react-aspnet-boilerplate]generator
       -react-aspnet-boilerplate - Starting point for building isomorphic
       React applications with ASP.NET Core 1, leveraging existing
       techniques.
     * [https://github.com/banderson/generator-redux]generator-redux - CLI
       tools for Redux: next-gen functional Flux/React with devtools.
     * [https://github.com/stylesuxx/generator-react-webpack-redux]generat
       or-react-webpack-redux - React Webpack Generator including Redux
       support.
     * [https://github.com/matthewmueller/socrates]socrates - Small (8kb),
       batteries-included Redux store to reduce boilerplate and promote
       good habits.

Miscellaneous

     * [https://github.com/jas-chen/redux-core]redux-core - Minimal Redux.

Learning Material

     * Redux's concepts
       [http://redux.js.org/]Redux official documentation does a great job
       at explaining Redux's core principles.
     * Why immutable data structures
       The
       [https://facebook.github.io/react/docs/advanced-performance.html]gu
       ide on performance of React's official documentation explains well
       what immutable data structures are and why they play an important
       role.
     * Side Effects
       [https://github.com/redux-loop/redux-loop]Redux Loop's readme gives
       a good insight on Side Effects in the context of Redux.

   Reading the aforementioned material will get you a good start for
   writing apps with Redux. If you are curious for more, check out
   following resources.
     * Functional Programming - Basics
       This
       [http://jaysoo.ca/2016/01/13/functional-programming-little-ideas/]p
       ost goes over basic concepts of functional programming while
       building a YouTube instant search demo app.
     * Reactive Programming
       This
       [https://gist.github.com/staltz/868e7e9bc2a7b8c1f754]introduction
       to Reactive Programming explains Reactive Programming with clarity.
     * Functional Programming - Going beyond
       Well written
       [https://medium.com/@chetcorcos/functional-programming-for-javascri
       pt-people-1915d8775504]article that talks about interesting
       computer science concepts implemented in functional languages and
       how these apply to JavaScript.
     * Monads
       Curious about monads? Wikipedia gives a good
       [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monad_(functional_programming)]overv
       iew on monads and
       [http://adit.io/posts/2013-04-17-functors,_applicatives,_and_monads
       _in_pictures.html]this article explains monads in more details with
       graphics and simple examples.

